    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/bfeb329b-a95f-49a7-9a7a-2877aa0b1142\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. nvim --clean\n2. source the following:\n```\nlet ns = nvim_create_namespace('')\ncall setline(1, '       ')\ncall setline(2, '')\ncall nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 1, 0, #{virt_text: [[\"\\t\\t\\tpanel = { enabled = false },\" ]], virt_text_pos: 'inline', hl_mode: 'replace'})\n```\n3. j\n4. i\n5. `<bs>`\n6. source the following:\n```\ncall nvim_buf_clear_namespace(0, 0, 0, -1)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFor the inline extmark text to fully dissapear\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.3 Release\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nDid not test\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nWinget",
